comments: Paul (GSW) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Paul (GSW) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects Okogie's (PHX) pass away. Any ensuing contact with Nurkic (PHX) as Paul secures the loose ball is incidental.
Looney (GSW) is established in a screening position in Okogie's (PHX) path and the contact is marginal as Okogie goes underneath the screen.
Okogie (PHX) legally contests Paul's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) extends his left forearm into Kuminga's (GSW) body, which affects his shot attempt near the rim.
After Durant (PHX) secures the rebound, Looney (GSW) and Thompson (GSW) reach for the ball and any contact with Durant's arm is marginal.
Kuminga (GSW) reaches in and makes contact to Booker's (PHX) body, which affects Booker's (PHX) SQBR on the perimeter.

Nurkic (PHX) establishes and re-establishes himself in a screening position in Kuminga's (GSW) path without delivering contact.  Nurkic briefly grasps Kuminga's arm after the two players engage and he immediately releases.
Booker (PHX) places his forearm against Kuminga (GSW) and releases from contact as he changes directions on the perimeter.
Looney (GSW) firms up in Booker's (PHX) path and marginal contact occurs to his upper thigh as Booker (PHX) goes over the pick.
Nurkic (PHX) extends his arm across Curry's (GSW) body, initiating contact that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Nurkic (PHX) places an arm against Kuminga's (GSW) side as he goes around the pick and the contact is marginal.

Booker (PHX) is moving legally along Paul's (GSW) path as Paul turns toward the rim, and their legs connect, causing Booker to lose his balance. From all available angles, Paul appears to pull his arm out from between them without applying force in the direction of Booker's movement.
Kuminga (GSW), Okogie (PHX) and Durant (PHX) connect while attempting to get to the rebound, and Kuminga tips the ball out to Curry (GSW).
Okogie (PHX) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Nurkic (PHX) establishes himself in Payton II's (GSW) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Nurkic (PHX) turns to roll and marginal contact occurs with Payton II (GSW) as he goes underneath the pick.

Thompson (GSW) jumps vertically to contest Nurkic's (PHX) play at the basket and and as he retreats away from Nurkic, incidental contact occurs when Nurkic normally extends his legs during his shooting motion.
Looney (GSW) establishes himself in Gordon's (PHX) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Booker (PHX) legally contests Paul's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) legally contests Thompson's (GSW) jump shot attempt.

Looney (GSW) reaches for the ball and grazes Okogie's (PHX) head during the rebound.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
